# Local environment — QA only, never production

## Rule

When developing locally (`expo start`, web on localhost, simulators, Expo Go):

- **API:** `EXPO_PUBLIC_API_ENV` must be `qa` or `localhost` — **never** `production`.
- **REST URL:** use `EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://mordobo-api-qa.onrender.com` or `http://localhost:3000`.
- **Do not** set `EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL_PROD` or prod Render URLs in `.env`.
- **Supabase:** use the project tied to the **QA** API backend — not the production Supabase project (`xxvjunhjerhlxhmarelr`).

Production URLs belong only in:

- `eas.json` → `production` profile
- Netlify / GitHub Actions for deployed web builds
- EAS Secrets (not committed `.env`)

## Correct local `.env`

```env
EXPO_PUBLIC_ENV=development
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_ENV=qa
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://mordobo-api-qa.onrender.com
```

## Forbidden in local `.env`

```env
# ❌ NEVER for local development
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_ENV=production
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL_PROD=https://mordobo-api-prod.onrender.com
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://xxvjunhjerhlxhmarelr.supabase.co
```

## Code safety net

`utils/apiConfig.ts` forces QA in `__DEV__` if production is detected.
`utils/supabase.ts` blocks the production Supabase project ref in `__DEV__`.

## After editing `.env`

Restart Expo with cache clear: `npm run start -- -c`

Verify in Metro logs:

```
[API Config] API_ENV: qa
[API Config] API_BASE: https://mordobo-api-qa.onrender.com
```
